The paper proposes a method for collision avoidance for autonomous robots, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The method involves optimization using subgradient descent, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with navigating in challenging scenarios, which involves control systems (cs.SY). The proposed method is flexible and can support various robot motion models, which may involve machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper presents results using simulated robots, which may involve computer vision techniques for perception (cs.CV).
